'''GNU screen''' is a [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VT100 VT100] terminal multiplexer, default installed tool in [[SHR]]. The started terminal processes are [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Persistence_%28computer_science%29 persistent] and shareable.

It can, among others, be used for making [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virtual_terminal virtual terminal]s, and to do serial communication via a physical or virtual [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serial_port serial port] (typical RS-232):
*man screen

